Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Meanwhile in a food processor combine pancetta, garlic and parsley; pulse until finely ground. Add the mixture to a large skillet with olive oil and cook over medium heat for about 8 minutes. Stir in the Barilla Traditional sauce, one cup of water and season with salt and pepper. Cook the pasta according to package directions; drain and toss with the sauce. Stir in the cheese before serving.